Enquiry code for this property: 3142

A RARE SIZED 20 ACRE PROPERTY WITH 10M BY 10M SHED

30 MINUTES DRIVE TO CAIRNS CBD

10 MINUTE DRIVE TO KURANDA VILLAGE

MAINS POWER, 2 LARGE WATER TANKS AND BILLABONG WITH RUNNING CREEK


A unique property not to be presented again. 

A “Jewel in the Crown” offering the serenity of an exclusive private location. With the additional benefits and convenience of a Cairns city 30 minutes away by car. 

Close access to Cairns international and domestic airports as well as a leading University (James Cook University). This location offers cool mountain breezes and mild winters, and a quiet, private and lush green escape from city life.

You could enjoy the mild Tableland tropical summer months in bliss, and escape the Australia’s southern chilling winter months. 

Huge rainforest trees frame this picturesque setting and set it apart as one of the better properties in the Cairns Tablelands region.

 A much sort after location:

* a tropical paradise;
* World Heritage Great Barrier Reef and Wet Tropics on your doorstep; 
* huge 10 metre by 10 metre colorbond shed which has 3 roller doors, a single entry door and two sets of large windows on each side of shed for natural light. Would make an excellent work, storage or house conversion. mains power is connected to shed and the shed is also insulated with high quality roof insulation, designed from NASA technology.
* 9 metre by 6 metre cabin with French doors and timber windows great for extra storage or artist retreat;
* 3 metre by 3 metre galvanised garden tool shed;
* fresh water running creek on property that feeds into billabong;
* natural wildlife platypus's, turtles, kangaroos, etc on property;
* property is a natural corridor for the native animals travelling from the Tablelands to Kuranda and beyond;
* 5 acres cleared manicured grass and many fruit trees such as mango, lychee and other tropical fruits. All are well established and organic;
* 15 acres natural tropical forest;
* 20 minutes to James Cook University by car;
* Steiner School 15 minutes drive;
* Kuranda District College 15 minutes drive;
* Kuranda Arts Community;
* Kuranda Village 10 minutes drive boasting: Ambulance Service, Post Office, Supermarket, markets, sky rail, two pubs, medical clinic;
* Cairns Base Hospital 30 minutes drive away, 5 min by helicopter;
* 20 minutes drive from property to Smithfield Shopping Centre;
* average 25-26 daytime temperature in winter months, very low humidity all year round;
* temperature 7-10 degrees cooler than Cairns summer months;
* private secluded location
* suit boutique resort, horse property, or private get-away escape;
* can land a helicopter in the top paddock;
* international and domestic airports Cairns;
* 8km directly over the mountains from Cairns airport;
* 30-40 min drive from Cairns;
* equestrian riding school at beginning of road
* also public equestrian exercising area, tennis courts, and playground at beginning of road;
* general store and petrol station at beginning of road and
* school bus service


*Quiet, Peaceful and Secure Location.

Possible future potential for sub-division surveyor employed to survey the property into four, five acre lots.

